-- Vietnam's Equity Movers
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-04-05T05:35:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/vietnam-s-equity-movers.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11:30 a.m. break in Ho Chi
Minh City.  The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, gained 0.6 percent to 442.59. The  VN-30 Index (VN30) , a
free-float adjusted, market capitalization-weighted index of 30
stocks that have the highest market value and liquidity on the
bourse, increased 0.9 percent to 504.69.  Elcom Corp. (ELC)  , which offers telecommunications,
information technology and electronics products, advanced for a
fifth day, climbing 4.3 percent to 31,600 dong, poised for the
highest since Sept. 28. The company will pay a 2011 dividend of
800 dong a share on May 10, according to a statement on the
bourse’s website.  FPT Corp. (FPT)  , Vietnam’s biggest publicly traded
telecommunications and software company, rose 2.6 percent to
59,500 dong, headed for the highest close since February 17,
2011. The company will pay 2011 dividend of 2,000 dong per share
in the second quarter, it said in an exchange statement.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
